==English==
{{wikipedia|Xerxes|Xerxes (disambiguation)}}
===Etymology===
From {{der|en|grc|Ξέρξης}}, from {{der|en|peo|𐎧𐏁𐎹𐎠𐎼𐏁𐎠||ruler among kings|ts=Xšayāršā}}. {{doublet|en|Ahasuerus}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˈzɜːk.siːz/}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|zûrk'sēz}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈzɝksiːz/}}
===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|es}}
# {{lb|en|historical}} [[w:Xerxes_I_of_Persia|Xerxes I]], a Persian king of the Achaemenid dynasty who reigned 485-465 BC.
# {{lb|en|historical}} [[w:Xerxes_II_of_Persia|Xerxes II]], a Persian king who ruled for 45 days in 424 BC before being assassinated.
# {{non-gloss definition|{{given name|en|male|from=Old Persian}} mainly applied to historical and fictional characters.}}
